# TYPING RULE: move-vs-Copy ownership-transfer discipline.
#
# Prior art: Rust's ownership rule ("each value has one owner; assignment or
# by-value passing of a non-Copy value moves ownership out of the source
# binding, invalidating further use of the source" — The Rust Programming
# Language, Klabnik & Nichols, ch. 4.1 "What Is Ownership?") combined with
# the Copy-trait exemption (types implementing `Copy` are duplicated, not
# moved, on by-value use — Rust Reference, "Special types and traits: Copy").
# Formalized as the used-once/substructural typing discipline for non-Copy
# places (vs. the unrestricted-use discipline for Copy places) in Weiss,
# Patterson, Matsakis & Ahmed, "Oxide: The Essence of Rust" (arXiv:1903.00982),
# section 3's typing rule for a place expression's move.
#
# ggen template pattern this checks: packs/tcps-ffi-pack/templates/lib.rs.tmpl:43-77
# (選択する外部関数). gec:Local_要求 (bindingType PathType "選択要求", a struct — not
# Copy) is passed by value into 選択する(...) and is correctly modeled
# gec:MoveTransfer (gec:Edge_要求_move) — this rule recomputes that expectation
# from gec:bindingType and asserts it must match the declared
# gec:ownershipTransferKind. Grounded scope: this rule only checks edges whose
# gec:fromSite is a gec:LocalBinding (bindingType is asserted there); the
# corpus's one field-to-field Copy example (gec:Edge_取得権限_copy, u64 — Copy)
# sources from a gec:StructFieldSite, which the ontology does not attach a
# type to (see gec:StructFieldSite in ontology.ttl) — an honest modeling gap,
# not silently glossed over. Verified 2026-07-21: ASK=false against
# ontology.ttl+fixtures/gec-facts.ttl (the one exercised case, Local_要求,
# is correctly classified); ASK=true against an adversarial fixture asserting
# a Copy-eligible u32 local wrongly declared gec:MoveTransfer.
PREFIX gec: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/rust-dialect#>
ASK
WHERE {
  ?edge a gec:OwnershipEdge ;
        gec:ownershipTransferKind ?declaredKind ;
        gec:fromSite ?binding .
  ?binding a gec:LocalBinding ;
           gec:bindingType ?t .
  FILTER (?declaredKind IN (gec:MoveTransfer, gec:CopyTransfer))
  BIND(EXISTS {
    ?t a gec:PrimitiveType ; gec:primitiveName ?pn .
    FILTER(?pn IN ("u8","u16","u32","u64","usize","i8","i16","i32","i64","isize","bool","f32","f64","char"))
  } AS ?isCopyPrimitive)
  BIND(IF(?isCopyPrimitive, gec:CopyTransfer, gec:MoveTransfer) AS ?expectedKind)
  FILTER(?declaredKind != ?expectedKind)
}
